    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="105" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Unofficial.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Señor Romero</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Frederick W. Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexican Legation</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-09-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 20, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir:</hi> In answer to your unofficial note of
                            this date informing me that “you have noticed in a St. Louis paper a
                            letter alleged to be from some point on the frontier, stating that the
                            Marquis de Montholon, who is supposed to be a son of the French minister
                            here, had been taken prisoner in the State of Durango, and shot by his
                            captors,” and asking me to communicate to you any information I might
                            have received upon the subject, I have to say that I have received, as
                            yet, no information on the matter. Should I receive any, I will be very
                            glad to transmit it to you. If it should be agreeable to you I will ask
                            home for reliable information about that intelligence.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, very respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M. ROMERO.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Frederick</hi> W. <hi rend="smallcaps">Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.,
                                &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
